Israeli Stocks: Elbit Imaging, Bioline, Pluristem and WideMed

-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 
2011-09-07T15:05:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-07/israeli-stocks-bioline-widemed-shares-are-active-in-tel-aviv.html
Israel ’s TA-25 Index jumped the most
since April 2009, climbing 3.8 percent to 1,072.41 at the 4:30
p.m. close in  Tel Aviv . Investors traded about 1.41 billion
shekels ($382 million) of shares and convertible securities
today, according to Tel Aviv Stock Exchange data.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Bioline Rx Ltd. (BLRX)   advanced for the first time in
four days, increasing 2.7 percent to 1.241 shekels. The
biopharmaceutical company signed a license agreement with Ramot
at Tel Aviv University Ltd. for its BL-7050 treatment for
neuropathic and inflammatory pain.  Elbit Imaging Ltd. (EMIT)   declined to the lowest level
since at least December 1996 when Bloomberg began tracking the
shares, dropping 1.7 percent to 8.887 shekels. The notes of the
investor in real estate and the Series A and B notes of its
Plaza Centers NV subsidiary were lowered to ilBBB+/Negative from
ilA/Watch Negative at Standard & Poor’s Maalot.  Pluristem Therapeutics Inc. (PSTI)   rose the most in
almost two weeks, jumping 7.4 percent to 9.474 shekels. The
cell-therapy company said initial animal studies suggest its
cells can increase survival rates following exposure to lethal
doses of radiation.  WideMed (WDMD)  Ltd fell to the lowest since Aug. 8,
slumping 8.8 percent to 0.547 shekel. The provider of bio-
medical signal diagnostics and treatment is offering 4.5 million
shares for sale at 0.525 shekel each.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
